"{\"uid\": \"canberratimes.com.au-story-8759987-man-charged-but-no-sign-of-missing-olympic-medals\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Your digital subscription includes access to content from all our websites in your region.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 90, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Access unlimited news content and The Canberra Times app.\", \"from\": 92, \"to\": 149, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 126, \"end\": 144, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Canberra_Times\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Canberra Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Canberra_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Canberra_Times\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Premium subscribers also enjoy interactive puzzles and access to the digital version of our print edition - Today's Paper.\", \"from\": 150, \"to\": 272, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Police have charged a man for allegedly stealing four Olympic medals, but the hunt for the stolen medallions continues.\", \"from\": 274, \"to\": 393, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Loginor signup to continue reading  The medals, three gold and one silver from four successive Olympics were allegedly stolen from Oarsome Foursome rower Drew Ginn's car at Melbourne's Docklands.\", \"from\": 395, \"to\": 590, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 526, \"end\": 542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oarsome_Foursome\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Oarsome Foursome\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oarsome_Foursome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oarsome_Foursome\"}, {\"begin\": 549, \"end\": 558, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Drew_Ginn\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Drew Ginn\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Drew_Ginn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Drew_Ginn\"}, {\"begin\": 568, \"end\": 577, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\", \"score\": 0.9999999976930667, \"rank\": 2.2919916120972606e-09, \"text\": \"Melbourne\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\"}, {\"begin\": 580, \"end\": 589, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Docklands\", \"score\": 0.9997783161566466, \"rank\": 0.0002206775301671941, \"text\": \"Docklands\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Docklands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Docklands\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Police arrested 47-year-old Windsor man Luke Tones in Brunswick on Wednesday afternoon following a public appeal from police and Ginn.\", \"from\": 592, \"to\": 726, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 632, \"end\": 636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luke_Snyder\", \"score\": 0.9695810106166757, \"rank\": 0.03137078337700886, \"text\": \"Luke\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luke_Snyder\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luke_Snyder\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tones has been charged with theft from motor vehicle, obtain property by deception, obtain financial advantage by deception and handle stolen goods.\", \"from\": 728, \"to\": 876, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He will face Melbourne Magistrates' Court on November 29.\", \"from\": 878, \"to\": 935, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 891, \"end\": 919, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne_Magistrates'_Court\", \"score\": 0.9999999953233782, \"rank\": 4.676484108578119e-09, \"text\": \"Melbourne Magistrates' Court\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne_Magistrates'_Court\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne_Magistrates'_Court\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Neither the Olympic medals or any of the other allegedly stolen property have been recovered at this time,\\\" a police statement said.\", \"from\": 937, \"to\": 1070, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ginn said he had hidden the medals in a secure spot in his car, which was parked on Cumberland Street, after he had shown them at a school event more than a week earlier.\", \"from\": 1072, \"to\": 1242, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It must have been about five minutes, it dawned on me that I'd have been at a school event maybe 10 days before ... and then all of a sudden, I was like, 'Oh no',\\\" Ginn told reporters earlier on Wednesday.\", \"from\": 1244, \"to\": 1450, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Your heart sinks.\\\"\", \"from\": 1452, \"to\": 1471, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A wetsuit, a Go Pro camera and headphones were also allegedly stolen, but the rower said it was hard to put a dollar value on the medals.\", \"from\": 1473, \"to\": 1610, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's a hunk of metal - they are gold plated,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1612, \"to\": 1667, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's the reality.\", \"from\": 1669, \"to\": 1689, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But for me, it's just it's a horrible feeling to sort of think and imagine that medal will not potentially be in my family.\\\"\", \"from\": 1691, \"to\": 1816, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Oarsome Foursome was a series of Australian rowing Coxless Four crews, with Ginn taking part in latter combinations which won gold at the Atlanta 1996 Games and silver at London 2012.\", \"from\": 1818, \"to\": 2005, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1855, \"end\": 1865, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9686607241392238, \"rank\": 0.0323491247912334, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 1873, \"end\": 1885, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coxless_four\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.115094271426619e-49, \"text\": \"Coxless Four\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coxless_four\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coxless_four\"}, {\"begin\": 1993, \"end\": 2004, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.4959190596464595e-12, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ginn also won gold medals in pair events at Athens 2004 and Beijing 2008.\", \"from\": 2007, \"to\": 2080, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympian has shown his medals to more than 150 schools in the past two decades and hoped he would be able to do so again.\", \"from\": 2082, \"to\": 2207, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2086, \"end\": 2094, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999996807674, \"rank\": 3.194108411695881e-10, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I like the idea that these medals are medals for Australia,\\\" Ginn said.\", \"from\": 2209, \"to\": 2281, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2259, \"end\": 2268, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.999995665959274, \"rank\": 4.1360365122938274e-06, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's not just you as an athlete representing your country - you are representing every single person.\\\"\", \"from\": 2283, \"to\": 2386, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Australian Associated Press  Daily  Today's top stories curated by our news team.\", \"from\": 2388, \"to\": 24